-- Possibility of China Rate Increase Rising, Deutsche Bank's Jun Ma Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-12T02:16:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/possibility-of-china-rate-increase-rising-deutsche-bank-s-jun-ma-says.html
The possibility that China may raise
interest rates has risen following the increase in the bank
reserve requirement ratio, according to Deutsche Bank AG.  Pressure for an “asymmetric rate hike” or liberalization
of deposit rates will increase after the central bank raised the
reserve requirement ratio and given rising inflation in
September and recent rebound in stock and property prices,
Deustche Bank analysts led by Jun Ma said in a report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chua Kong Ho in Shanghai at 
